This paper deals with the design and analysis of a communication network, specifically a multiple-relay network, which involves information theory and networking concepts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves the use of multiple antennas, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the diversity-multiplexing tradeoff, which is a concept in control systems, suggesting the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper involves the use of multiple-antenna relays, which suggests the category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves the use of amplify-and-forward relaying, which is a common technique in communication networks, suggesting the category cs.COM (Computer Communications and Networks).
